#. <section class="sutta" id="sn23.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn23.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 23"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 23"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyamāravagga"
msgstr "2. About Māra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn23.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Māradhammasutta"
msgstr "12. A Māra-like Nature"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn23.12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn23.12:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, Venerable Rādha said to the Buddha:"

# BB has “subject to Māra”. In this context, it’s a tempting rendering. But as usual, I simply don’t think that’s what it means. It doesn’t mean, “Things over which Mara wields power”. It means “things that share a similar quality or nature to Mara”. My rendering is clumsy, but I think it captures the sense better.
msgctxt "sn23.12:1.3"
msgid "“‘māradhammo, māradhammo’ti, bhante, vuccati."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘Māra-like nature’."

msgctxt "sn23.12:1.4"
msgid "Katamo nu kho, bhante, māradhammo”ti?"
msgstr "What is a Māra-like nature?”"

msgctxt "sn23.12:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Rūpaṃ kho, rādha, māradhammo, vedanā māradhammo, saññā māradhammo, saṅkhārā "
"māradhammo, viññāṇaṃ māradhammo."
msgstr ""
"“Rādha, form has a Māra-like nature. Feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness have a Māra-like nature."

msgctxt "sn23.12:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn23.12:1.7"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn23.12:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
